UNIT 3 â€“ Introduction to Threat Modelling
Unit Overview

This unit introduced threat modelling concepts and distinguished between threats and vulnerabilities, reviewing techniques such as STRIDE, DREAD, attack trees, and PASTA.

Artefacts

STRIDE vs DREAD comparison table

Threat vs vulnerability notes

Summary post contribution

Individual Contribution

I analysed multiple threat modelling frameworks and contributed to the collaborative discussion summary.

Reflection

This unit highlighted the value of threat modelling as a proactive security practice. Comparing different models showed that no single framework is universally applicable. Instead, model selection must reflect system complexity, attacker capability, and organisational goals. This insight guided my later use of hybrid approaches when analysing real-world systems.

References

Shevchenko, N. et al. (2018). Threat Modeling: A Summary of Available Methods.
